N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1242.6 - Public wharf, definition of

State Regulations
A wharf, pier, quay, or other portion of of the terminal, designated and operated temporarily or permanently by the Port Authority as a
public wharf for the mooring of watercraft, the loading and unloading of
passengers, and the loading, unloading, handling and holding of
cargo. Notes
